      <div class="msgContentFrame">I don't know about everyone else, but I'm really tired of accepting local guildleves where it is clearly not mathematically possible to complete the quest.  I have a full crafting gear setup, 5 disciplines of the hand at level 10, which means I have quite a few abilities to use during synthesis, and always use master guild support.   <br /> <br />I know there is a version update in the future which will allow us to cancel these quests, but that still is going to waste one of my local leves every time I find one I cannot complete.  Considering that these are different from regional leves (the difficulty level cannot be adjusted), I really wish that SE would simply not offer us any quests that we couldn't complete at least 50% of the time.  Otherwise I'm stuck doing 6 synths I know I'm going to fail and get nothing out of, per accepted leve.  Aka I'm potentionally wasting 30-45 minutes every time I try new local leves.  Please change this SE.  Atm, your crafting system is more fun than your combat system...</div>
